OL,3,CPrisons minister says community orders
OL,4,Cneed to be 'trusted more' by courts
OL,6,F"We don't want suspended sentences,"
OL,7,Fone audience member told him. "The law
OL,8,Fsays a community order is a direct
OL,9,Falternative to custody. We need
OL,10,Fmassive publicity, we need Government
OL,11,Fbranding and I beg you to say it."
OL,13,FMr Timpson expressed sympathy with her
OL,14,Fview replying: "I completely agree
OL,15,Fwith you about the positive impact of
OL,16,Fcommunity sentencing but I think it
OL,17,Fneeds to be trusted more by the
OL,18,Fcourts."
